<center><font size=7><b>Batman 1</b></font></center>
<center>Number of entries found: 4</center><p>
<center>
<table width=600>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Tips</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>To complete the game, once you have all the seven parts, find the room
where the pieces are all assembled on two stump like posts.  Use the parcel
to jump onto the Batcraft, move to the front of the car and push onto the
front of the cockpit.  The tune will play, and that's the end of the game.
<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In the boots room, you can avoid the henchmen very easily using the
following method.  It is possible to balance on the edge of the blocks and
walk past them, without touching.  in order to get back use the same
technique.  Familiarity with the game is the key.  Make a map
 <i>(Glen Robins, Mark Ruttle. in Your Sinclair issue 8)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Multiface pokes</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD><b>(Not sure which version of Batman this is for)</b>
This can be found in <a href="ftp://ftp.void.jump.org/pub/sinclair/magazines/SinclairUser/Issue117/Tape/">this issue of Tips Amazing</a> in the Multiface Hacks section.
 <i>(Cover Tape in Sinclair User issue 117)</i> 

<br><hr>
<table border="0">
<tr>
<td WIDTH="200" ALIGN="LEFT"><B><U>DESCRIPTION</B></U></TD>
<td WIDTH="200" ALIGN="LEFT"><B><U>POKE(s)</B></U></TD>
</TR>
<tr><td>Infinite Lives</td><td>36798,0</td></tr>
<tr><td>Fast Batman</td><td>26174,201</td></tr>
<tr><td>Fast Batman (in empty rooms)</td><td>26052,58</td></tr>
<tr><td>Immunity</td><td>39908,201</td></tr>
</table>
<BR><BR><B>With immunity on, you can get stuck in rooms where you would normally
die if you fell into certain bits. If&nbsp;this happens, enter POKE 33908,192 to switch
immunity back off. Then when you die, switch it back on</b>
<BR>
The "Fast Batman" POKEs only makes you go faster in empty rooms. Try it
combined with a "Go Faster" - ZOOM!!!
<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <i>(Gerard Sweeney in Hack Attack III)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Type-in hacks</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>This can be found in <a href="ftp://ftp.void.jump.org/pub/sinclair/magazines/SinclairUser/Issue95/Tape/">this issue of Poke City</a>.
 <i>(Cover Tape in Sinclair User issue 95)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
